<section class="section" id="about">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <h2 class="section-heading">What is the REACH Study?</h2>
    <div class="about-layout">
      <div class="about-text">
        <p>
          REACH stands for Research and Engagement for Advancing Chronic pain Healthcare. It's a study at Johns Hopkins that's looking at new ways to help people with long-lasting back pain.
        </p>
        <p>
          Here's the idea: pain isn't just physical. Stress, sleep, mood — they all play a part. A psychologist can teach you real skills to manage your pain and feel more in control. But most people never get the chance to work with one.
        </p>
        <p>
          That's what this study is about. We want to make it easier for you to get this kind of help — and we want to learn how to do it better for everyone.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-image">
        <img
          src="/images/about.webp"
          alt="A man focused on his laptop at a desk at home"
          width="800"
          height="533"
          loading="lazy"
          class="about-photo"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  p {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .about-layout {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .about-photo {
    border-radius: 12px;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    object-fit: cover;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .about-layout {
      flex-direction: row;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 2.5rem;
    }

    .about-text {
      flex: 1;
    }

    .about-image {
      flex: 0 0 280px;
    }
  }
</style>
